# QWERTY US + Compose key (Right Alt) for typing accents — é è ê ç à etc.
# Usage: tap Right Alt, release, then a sequence — e.g. ' e -> é, ` e -> è, , c -> ç.
#
# We set GNOME's xkb-options (dconf) rather than calling setxkbmap directly:
# Regolith/GNOME re-applies its own keyboard settings after i3 starts (login,
# resume, settings change) and would clobber a bare setxkbmap, dropping
# compose:ralt and leaving only ctrl:swapcaps. Writing the gsettings key makes
# GNOME itself carry the Compose option, so it sticks across re-applications and
# boots. exec_always re-asserts it (and triggers an immediate re-apply) on every
# i3 start/reload. Caps<->Ctrl swap kept.
exec_always --no-startup-id gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.input-sources xkb-options "['ctrl:swapcaps', 'compose:ralt']"
